  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile, W-ON-01 trigger)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) operating conditions. The intended use is prediction of absolute hemolysis index for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5 to support a 510(k) submission. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all 13 credibility factors; seven factors were formally assessed and six were flagged as epistemic gaps. All assessed factors achieved the required gradation levels under the Minimal-profile evaluation. Decision: Accepted. NOTE: hasContextOfUse is intentionally absent (W-ON-01); use-scope information appears only in this prose and in the bound Requirement and Claim nodes.",
